<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-02-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-02-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="149" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-02-26"><hi rend="italic">February 26,
                            1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Saw Lord Rosebery to-day. Draft of law to give fall effect to the award and
                        regulations mailed to Sir Julian Pauncefote last Saturday. Lord Rosebery
                        assures intent to execute award without evasion or hesitation. Have sent him
                        note deprecating delay and impressively urging immediate conclusion of the
                        convention.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>